x=seq(0.1,20,0.001)
yvalue<-dgamma(x,3,1)
x.mean<-3*1
x.median<- qgamma(0.5,3,1)
plot(x,dgamma(x,3,1),main=
       "Gamma Probability Density Function",ylab = "P",xlab = "x",type = "l") + abline(v=x.mean,col="red") + abline(v=x.median,col="blue")

legend("topright",c("mean","median"),col = c("red","blue"),lty = c(1,1))

a<-rep(NA,1000)
b<-rep(NA,1000)
for (i in 1:1000) {
        c=rgamma(100,3,1)
        a[i]=mean(c)
        b[i]=exp(mean(log(c)))
        
}
plot(a,b,main="geometic and arithmetic mean for gamma distribution",xlab="Arithmetic Mean",ylab="Geometic Mean")
abline(0,1)

hist(x=(a-b),main="Difference between Geometic and Arithmetic mean for gamma distribution ",xlab="Difference")

part 3

relationship <- function(sample,size){
  a<-rep(NA,size)
  b<-rep(NA,size)
  diff<-rep(NA,size)
  c<-NA
  for (i in 1:size) {
    c=sample(sample,size,replace = TRUE)
    a[i]=log(mean(c))
    b[i]=mean(log(c))
    diff[i]=a[i]-b[i]
  }
  mean(diff)
  #diff
  }
relationship(1000,100)
## [1] 0.3138246

By running this simulation, we can see that they are not equal. Since the mean difference is positive, the log (E[X]) is greater than E[log (X)]. This simulation has ran for a 100 samples of size 1000. The diff is the difference between those two value.
